DOCUMENT();
loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "Parser.pl",
  "freemanMacros.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);
$context = Context();

TEXT(beginproblem());
@list = qw(\frac{\pi}{6} \frac{\pi}{4} \frac{\pi}{3} \frac{\pi}{2});
@upps = qw(\frac{1}{2} \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2} \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2} 1);
@anss = (Compute("6 * pi * ((1/2)**5) / 5"), Compute("6 * pi * ((sqrt(2)/2)**5) / 5") ,Compute("6 * pi * ((sqrt(3)/2)**5) / 5"),Compute("6 * pi  / 5"));
@anspr = qw(6\pi\frac{\left(\frac{1}{2}\right)^5}{5} 6\pi\frac{\left(\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}\right)^5}{5} 6\pi\frac{\left(\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}\right)^5}{5} \frac{6\pi}{5});


$l = random(0,3);
$a = $list[$l];

$upp = $upps[$l];

$ans = $anss[$l];
$ansp = $anspr[$l];

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT
\{ textbook_ref_exact("Rogawski ET 2e", "11.2","32") \}
Compute the surface area of the surface generated by revolving the astroid with parametrization \( c(t) = ( \cos^3 t, \, \sin^3 t) \) about the x-axis for \( 0 \le t \le $a \)
$PAR
\{ ans_rule() \}
$PAR
END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

ANS($ans->cmp);

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR
$SOL
We have \( x(t) = \cos^3 t, \, y(t) = \sin^3 t, \, x'(t) = -3 \cos^2 t \sin t, \, y'(t) = 3 \sin^2 t \cos t \).  Hence,
\[ x'(t)^2 + y'(t)^2 = 9 \cos^4 t \sin^2 t + 9 \sin^4 t \cos^2 t = 9 \cos^2 t \sin^2 t \left( \cos^2 t + \sin^2 t \right) = 9 \cos^2 t \sin^2 t \]
Using the formula for the surface area we get
\[ S = 2 \pi \int ^{$a} _0 y(t) \sqrt{ x'(t)^2 + y'(t)^2 } \, dt = 2 \pi \int ^{$a} _0 \sin^3 t \cdot 3 \cos t \sin t \, dt = 6 \pi \int ^{$a} _0 \sin^4 t \cos t \, dt \]
We compute the integral using the substitution \( u = \sin t, \, du = \cos t\, dt \).  We obtain
\[ S = 6 \pi \int ^{$upp} _0 u^4 \, du = 6 \pi \frac{u^5}{5} \mid ^{$upp} _0 = $ansp \approx \{$ans\} \]
END_SOLUTION

